The government of Lagos State has shut the Redeemers Nursery and Primary School, Ogba. The school, according to Folasade Adefisayo, the Commissioner of Education, will remain closed, pending an administrative investigation of its operations and procedures as well as the conduct of its officials – in line with schools’ safety standards and guidelines. In the statement signed by the commissioner as pasted on the Lagos State Government’s Facebook, the investigation is a sequel to the death of a five-year-old pupil, who is suspected of having drowned during a swimming lesson while in the custody of the school. The police are investigating the matter. It reads in part, “A preliminary probe by the Office of Education Quality Assurance of the Ministry has shown that the Redeemers Nursery and Primary School, Ogba, is yet to conclude its registration and is, therefore, not yet an approved school. She posted: “The Ministry is concerned about the safety of the pupils, hence the need for intervention. The school will remain closed until all the necessary approval processes are concluded. Parents are advised to note the closure and wait for the conclusion of the administrative investigation.,” it concluded.